<subSubSection id="D984653DFFC0FFBDF4CBFCE74751C9E3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="912136B6FFC0FFBDF4CBFCE74751C9E3" blockId="34.[151,1436,807,1229]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF4CBFCE74575C957" bold="true" box="[151,273,807,832]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body strongly stellate (R/r=3.5â€“5.0), arms elongate, strap-like to triangular in shape. Interradial arcs acute. Arm rectangular in cross-section. Abactinal plates abutted, ranging ranging from flat to convex, covered with a distinct continuous cover of granules. Marginal plates broadly quadrate in outline forming discrete frame around abactinal-lateral outline of body. Marginal plate surface covered by continuous cover of granules Actinal region small, covered by granules. Papulae present between marginal and actinal plate contact. Furrow spines blunt, relatively few, with variable subambulacral armature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D984653DFFC0FFBDF49BFC3F40F6CEDA" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="912136B6FFC0FFBDF49BFC3F40F6CEDA" blockId="34.[151,1436,807,1229]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF49BFC3F452BCE0F" bold="true" box="[199,335,1023,1048]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF50BFBC145CECE0F" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[343,426,1025,1048]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Fromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF50BFBC145CECE0F" box="[343,426,1025,1048]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nominally includes 16 species (
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFC0FFBDF744FC3F407BCE0F" author="Mah, C. &amp; Hansson, H." box="[792,1055,1023,1048]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="2017" refId="ref72624" refString="Mah, C. &amp; Hansson, H. (2011) Fromia Gray, 1840. In: Mah, C. L. (2017). World Asteroidea database. Accessed from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / asteroidea / aphia. php? p = taxdetails &amp; id = 123311 (accessed 12 November 2017)" type="book chapter" year="2011">Mah &amp; Hansson, 2011</bibRefCitation>
), many of which, such as 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF115FBC1457BCE2A" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Fromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="milleporella">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF115FBC1457BCE2A" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fromia milleporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are commonly encountered and widely occurring throughout the Indo-Pacific region (
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFC0FFBDF17BFBE44540CE77" author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref69107" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of Shallow-water Indo-West Pacific Echinoderms. British Museum (Natural History) Publications 690. British Museum (Natural History), London, ix + 238, 31 pls." type="book" year="1971">Clark and Rowe, 1971</bibRefCitation>
). A total of eight 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF5A9FB89462CCE77" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[501,584,1097,1120]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Fromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF5A9FB89462CCE77" box="[501,584,1097,1120]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. are known to occur in the Indian Ocean (see Appendix 1). Although historically placed within the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF5AEFBAC46C7CE92" box="[498,675,1132,1157]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophidiasteridae</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFC0FFBDF6B6FBAC47BECE93" author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[746,986,1132,1157]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref69107" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of Shallow-water Indo-West Pacific Echinoderms. British Museum (Natural History) Publications 690. British Museum (Natural History), London, ix + 238, 31 pls." type="book" year="1971">Clark &amp; Rowe 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFC0FFBDF7B5FBAC40D4CE93" author="Clark, A. M." box="[1001,1200,1132,1157]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="187 - 366" refId="ref69077" refString="Clark, A. M. (1993) An index of names of recent Asteroidea-Part 2: Valvatida. E chinoderm Studies, 4, 187 - 366." type="journal article" year="1993">A.M. Clark 1993</bibRefCitation>
) molecular data has shown that 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF541FB514514CEBF" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[285,368,1169,1192]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Fromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF541FB514514CEBF" box="[285,368,1169,1192]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF603FB4F4795CEBF" authority="(Mah &amp; Foltz 2011)" authorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[607,1009,1167,1192]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">
Goniasteridae (
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFC0FFBDF750FB4F478ECEBF" author="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W." box="[780,1002,1167,1192]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="769 - 788" refId="ref72510" refString="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W. (2011) Molecular Phylogeny of the Valvatacea (Asteroidea, Echinodermata). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 161, 769 - 788. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2010.00659. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Mah &amp; Foltz 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Other recent taxonomic adjustments (such as the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFC0FFBDF5E0FB74462BCEDB" authorityName="H.L.Clark" authorityYear="1921" box="[444,591,1204,1228]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Austrofromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFC0FFBDF5E0FB74462BCEDB" box="[444,591,1204,1228]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Austrofromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are mentioned below with the appropriate species.
</paragraph>
